      "message": "One would need to also pass in the script and language to assume to get a good answer. Under the hood these are always four byte tags which could be passed here as strings. Alternately a bcp47 string could be passed, which may actually be better. Probably whatever is easier to obtain.\n\nNote that one would already have needed to have broken up a longer string into parts which each have a single language/script for this to work well, so that would need to be a separate pass. Alternately this call could be modified to return this additional information (though that might be heavy). If this determines runs of language/script as well, there would still be a need to pass in a stack of bcp47 codes as context.",
